  where rank(row, j) = 1 + |{ c in [0, D): X[row,c] > X[row,j] or (X[row,c] == X[row,j] and c <= j) }| - 1
  That is, rank is the count of elements >= with the defined stable tie-break (c <= j), equivalent to ngt as counted below.

