  Proof: Each of the first m = min(n_directions, p) threads writes v[t] = d_directions[t] with no overlap.
  A single __syncthreads ensures visibility to all threads. m == p because stride is a power of two
  and p <= n_directions. No later write modifies v[], so it remains valid.

Invariant I1 (before storing d_output[i0]):
